data.text:
Rolo Tomassi are an experimental mathcore band from Sheffield.

Formed in 2005, the band have released five studio albums to date, the most recent being the critically acclaimed 'Where Myth Comes Memory' in 2022.

Rolo Tomassi will headline London's Electric Ballroom on February 15, 2023. Catch them live by checking tour dates and ticket information below on Stereoboard.

Nobody makes music quite like Rolo Tomassi. Since forming in Sheffield in 2005, they have morphed from kids playing glitchy mathcore to where they are now: a band trading in heavy music free from the constraints we might usually expect.
